With one notable exception on the southern county line, Wyandotte County consistently hosts some of the worst barbeque joints in the greater KC barbeplex. Big Q Barbeque absolutely blows that stereotype to bits and pieces. I dropped by for lunch and had a simple brisket sandwich, fries, and a soda pop. The sandwich was overwhelmingly generous in size. Perfectly smoked and as tender as one could hope. I’m eager to get back and sample other meats. If Big Q can do ribs and burnt ends as well as their brisket, this place is going to be a star. Maybe I missed a cue on one of the several menus posted around the restaurant, but I wish there was a lunch special. The brisket sandwich, ala carte fries, and soda… and tip (this should be a strict counter-serve set up) ran $15. Even considering the generous portion, that’s just too much for a very casual, minimal service barbeque joint. I’m not quibbling about value, I’m recommending an budget-minded option. All that aside, I’ll be back up to the Dot soon and familiarize myself with more of Big Que’s fare.

Really don't want to give this review-give up hidden secret!  Hosted 2 food critics in town recently that know BBQ in all areas of country, and rated this excellent.  Burnt ends trimmed of fat-best tried yet, meat is smoky and seasoned. 2 sauces for sweet or spicy tastes.  All sides great and big portions! Slaw is 'creamy', not too sweet, beans are smoky with meat bits, all types of fries were hot and fresh-steak fries, waffle, seasoned, etc. BEST onion rings-crispy panko crust, versus oily battered, etc.  Plus, if not sold out already for themselves as take-out by the whole, great deserts!!!  LOVE the pies, big carrot cake squares.!!  Highly recommend the burnt end brisket dinner with 2 sides for under 12.00 dollars, and will have leftover for lunch tomorrow!  Excellent service for a small place-very accommodating, no long waits like Oklahoma Joe's. Can seat yourself, or order at counter. 10-15 minute wait? Also, we call in and always ready according to time to travel from Johnson County.  Small clean place. Granite table tops, sun room/glass front. Outside dining area, big t.v.'s for games, etc..  I KNOW I am going to regret sharing this post!

Our favorite KC BBQ place for 35 plus years was Quicks 7th Street BBQ.  When they closed up a few years ago, we thought that was the end of our favorite place to eat.  My husband and I tried numerous bbq joints in KC  after they closed , but none compared.  THEN, I found out the owners son had a place called Big Q BBQ!  Yesterday for the first time I tried them out and I have to say, " Like father, like son!"  Oh how I missed the homemade bbq sauce of theirs, to the point I bought 2 bottles to bring home!  My sandwich was just as I remember it, steak fries, beans, ahhhhhh.  Makes me want to make another trip from St Joe down there again tonight! They have great portions, but all of the meat has no rub or smoke flavor at all.  I have eaten at roughly 70%-80% of the BBQ restaurants in KC (I love BBQ) and wanted to try Big Q because I had not been there, I was disappointed.  I ordered a two meat sandwich with beans and a side rib.  The beef was moist and tender, but there was no smoke flavor.  The pork was grey (I thought it was the beef initially) and it also had no smoke ring or rub flavor in it.  The rib was solid, tender and a lot of meat on it, but again, not much smoke flavor and no rub.  The beans tasted good, but they tasted like they had come from a can and had some spices and beef added.  I tried to doctor the meat with the sauce, but the sauce had no flavor either, tasted like runny ketchup.  I hate leaving terrible reviews, but if you like Joes KC, Jack Stack, etc you will likely not have a good experience here.  If you are driving by here and want bbq, drive a mile or so and go to Woodyard.  Maybe I had a bad experience, there are other good reviews out there, but I'm not willing to try going back.  The service was great and the place was clean, I just did not enjoy the food.  They were almost empty at 12pm as well, 4 other people were in the restaurant over a 20 minute window.
